[[meta title="Apache2 Vhost logging"]]

After long last, the Debian package introduces:

	nox:/etc/apache2% grep vhost apache2.conf
	LogFormat "%v:%p %h %l %u %t \"%r\" %>s %b \"%{Referer}i\" \"%{User-Agent}i\"" vhost_combined
	CustomLog /var/log/apache2/other_vhosts_access.log vhost_combined

But the el-cheapo virtual hosting `VirtualDocumentRoot /srv/www/%0` [setups do
not have ServerNames
setup](http://www.debian-administration.org/users/lee/weblog/12). So what you
really need is:

	LogFormat "%{Host}i:%p %h %l %u %t \"%r\" %>s %b \"%{Referer}i\" \"%{User-Agent}i\"" vhost_combined
